16.43.030.   Fireplaces and wood-burning appliances.
(a) 2025 California Green Building Code Section 4.503 is amended to read as follows:
4.503.1.   General.
Any installed gas fireplace shall be a direct-vent sealed combustion type. Any
installed wood stove or pellet stove shall comply with U.S. EPA New Source
Performance Standards (NSPS) emission limits as applicable, and shall have a
permanent label indicating they are certified to meet the emission limit.
This section shall not apply to the repair, reconstruction or replacement of any
lawful, existing wood-burning appliance.
